==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eft
<hw>Eft</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>efete</ets>
lizard. See <er>Newt</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>A European lizard of the genus <gen>Seps</gen>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>A salamander, esp. the European smooth newt (<spn>Triton
punctatus</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eft</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Eft
<hw>Eft</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>eft</ets>,
<ets>⟦ae⟧ft</ets>, again, back, afterward. See <er>Aft</er>,
<er>After</er>.]</ety> <def>Again; afterwards; soon; quickly.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I wold never <qex>eft</qex> comen into the snare.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj></p>

<p><ent>Eftsoons</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Eftsoon</ent>⟦br⟧
